{"image_id": "NSC_2005_page_54", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "K22", "bbox": [621.3, 1568.8, 658.4, 1589.5]}, {"text": "2004 Compared with 2003", "bbox": [150.0, 188.3, 412.3, 213.7]}, {"text": "Net income in 2004 of $923 million, or $2.31 per diluted share, was up $388 million, or 73%, compared", "bbox": [150.0, 235.8, 1111.1, 261.2]}, {"text": "with net income of $535 million, or $1.37 per diluted share, in 2003.  Results in 2003 included a", "bbox": [150.0, 262.0, 1039.6, 287.5]}, {"text": "$10 million, or 3 cents per share, gain from discontinued operations (see Note 17) and a $114 million, or", "bbox": [150.0, 288.3, 1114.6, 313.7]}, {"text": "29 cents per share, benefit related to the cumulative effect of changes in accounting principles (see", "bbox": [150.0, 314.8, 1059.6, 340.2]}, {"text": "Note 1).  Income from continuing operations before accounting changes was $923 million, or $2.31 per", "bbox": [150.0, 341.0, 1104.0, 366.5]}, {"text": "diluted share, in 2004, compared with $411 million, or $1.05 per diluted share, in 2003.  The increase in", "bbox": [150.0, 367.5, 1110.8, 393.0]}, {"text": "2004 was the result of higher income from railway operations and also included a $53 million net noncash", "bbox": [150.0, 393.8, 1130.1, 419.2]}, {"text": "gain from the Conrail Corporate Reorganization (see Note 5).  In addition, the comparisons were affected", "bbox": [150.0, 420.3, 1122.6, 445.7]}, {"text": "by the costs of a voluntary separation program (see Note 11) and the impairment of certain", "bbox": [150.0, 446.5, 987.7, 472.0]}, {"text": "telecommunications assets (see Note 6) in 2003, which combined to reduce net income in that year by", "bbox": [150.0, 472.8, 1090.6, 498.2]}, {"text": "$119 million, or 30 cents per diluted share.", "bbox": [150.0, 499.3, 550.0, 524.7]}, {"text": "DETAILED RESULTS OF OPERATIONS", "bbox": [150.0, 571.5, 580.8, 597.0]}, {"text": "Railway Operating Revenues", "bbox": [150.0, 619.5, 441.0, 645.0]}, {"text": "Railway operating revenues were $8.5 billion in 2005, $7.3 billion in 2004 and $6.5 billion in 2003.  The", "bbox": [150.0, 667.0, 1118.9, 692.5]}, {"text": "following table presents a three-year comparison of revenues, volume and average revenue per unit by", "bbox": [150.0, 693.3, 1094.6, 718.7]}, {"text": "market group.", "bbox": [150.0, 719.5, 284.2, 745.0]}, {"text": "Revenues", "bbox": [440.3, 772.8, 520.7, 793.6]}, {"text": "Units", "bbox": [735.2, 772.8, 782.5, 793.6]}, {"text": "Revenue per Unit", "bbox": [948.8, 772.8, 1131.5, 793.6]}, {"text": "2005", "bbox": [365.5, 794.3, 407.9, 815.1]}, {"text": "2004", "bbox": [459.3, 794.3, 501.7, 815.0]}, {"text": "2003", "bbox": [553.0, 794.3, 595.4, 815.0]}, {"text": "2005", "bbox": [646.8, 794.3, 689.2, 815.0]}, {"text": "2004", "bbox": [740.5, 794.3, 782.9, 815.0]}, {"text": "2003", "bbox": [831.3, 794.3, 873.7, 815.0]}, {"text": "2005", "bbox": [925.0, 794.3, 967.4, 815.0]}, {"text": "2004", "bbox": [1021.8, 794.3, 1064.2, 815.0]}, {"text": "2003", "bbox": [1115.5, 794.3, 1157.9, 815.0]}, {"text": "($ in millions)", "bbox": [424.7, 815.5, 536.0, 836.3]}, {"text": "(in thousands)", "bbox": [702.6, 815.5, 815.3, 836.3]}, {"text": "($ per unit)", "bbox": [994.8, 815.5, 1085.2, 836.3]}, {"text": "Coal", "bbox": [142.5, 858.5, 182.7, 879.3]}, {"text": "$ 2,115", "bbox": [348.8, 858.5, 424.7, 879.3]}, {"text": "$ 1,728", "bbox": [442.5, 858.5, 518.4, 879.3]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [536.3, 858.5, 545.6, 879.3]}, {"text": "1,500", "bbox": [565.0, 858.5, 612.2, 879.3]}, {"text": "1,735.4", "bbox": [644.8, 858.5, 706.0, 879.3]}, {"text": "1,690.8", "bbox": [738.5, 858.5, 799.7, 879.3]}, {"text": "1,614.6", "bbox": [826.5, 858.5, 887.7, 879.3]}, {"text": "$ 1,219", "bbox": [905.6, 858.5, 981.5, 879.3]}, {"text": "$ 1,022", "bbox": [999.3, 858.5, 1075.3, 879.3]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [1093.1, 858.5, 1102.5, 879.3]}, {"text": "929", "bbox": [1141.6, 858.5, 1174.8, 879.3]}, {"text": "General merchandise:", "bbox": [142.5,